      "text": "wsgi.py\nconcurrency -> more control to OS\nasync await -> more control to code\n\nwsgi.py -> howmany workers -> worker can be decided by\n    1 no of cores in our system\n    2 RAM Size\n\nin each worker inside wsgi a request should be complete first then only other request will be handled\nif 1 request is stuck on loop then that worker cant take another request\n\nasync await can run multiple request using await using uvicorn, fastapi uses that thats why it is fast\n\n\nWSGI ->\n\nClient -> gunicorn -> worker -> takes request -> 1 worker will complete 1 request first only then it can take other\n\nASGI\n\nClient → Gunicorn → Uvicorn worker → ASGI app (FastAPI / Django ASGI) \nGunicorn just spawns workers.\nAsync capability comes from Uvicorn, not Gunicorn itself.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "wsgi.py\nconcurrency -> more control to OS\nasync await -> more control to code\n\nwsgi.py -> howmany workers -> worker can be decided by\n    1 no of cores in our system\n    2 RAM Size\n\nin each worker inside wsgi a request should be complete first then only other request will be handled\nif 1 request is stuck on loop then that worker cant take another request\n\nasync await can run multiple request using await using uvicorn, fastapi uses that thats why it is fast\n\n\nWSGI ->\n\nClient -> gunicorn -> worker -> takes request -> 1 worker will complete 1 request first only then it can take other\n\nASGI\n\nClient → Gunicorn → Uvicorn worker → ASGI app (FastAPI / Django ASGI) \nGunicorn just spawns workers.\nAsync capability comes from Uvicorn, not Gunicorn itself.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "cweuhsExoCQ6mEYaD2RVm",
      "type": "text",
