      "updated": 1775226369120,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The main reason is:\nWeb servers and Python applications speak different languages. WSGI acts as a translator between them.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The main reason is:\nWeb servers and Python applications speak different languages. WSGI acts as a translator between them.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "D5NqcL6KtgQgB2ombyFIQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2000.1342546076967,
      "y": -246.8711271569191,
      "width": 891,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEf",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 807739499,
      "version": 519,
      "versionNonce": 1192862305,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775226369120,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1️⃣ First Understand the Problem\n    A web server like Nginx or Apache HTTP Server only understands HTTP protocol.\n    Example request from browser:",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1️⃣ First Understand the Problem\n    A web server like Nginx or Apache HTTP Server only understands HTTP protocol.\n    Example request from browser:",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "9fCwfTIBaNXFrPg78ie2G",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2039.3530046076967,
      "y": -132.6055021569191,
      "width": 891,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEg",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1241108549,
      "version": 534,
      "versionNonce": 177270831,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775226369120,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "GET /users HTTP/1.1\nHost: example.com\n\nBut your Python app (like Django or Flask) understands Python code, not raw HTTP.\nSo the question is:\nHow will HTTP requests become Python function calls?\nThis is where WSGI comes in.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "GET /users HTTP/1.1\nHost: example.com\n\nBut your Python app (like Django or Flask) understands Python code, not raw HTTP.\nSo the question is:\nHow will HTTP requests become Python function calls?\nThis is where WSGI comes in.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
